Craig Jeeves was alerted to the fire in his Wandin North home in Melbourne early Monday morning when his pet cat screamed at him and woke him up.

 'She jumped on my head and was screaming at me,' he told the Nine Network.

CFA operations manager Jason Lawrence said it was just after one o'clock this morning the brigade from Wandin responded to the fire.

Fire Crews, who found Mr Jeeves in the bushes outside his home when they arrived, said he was very lucky to be alive.

'The building was largely involved in fire, flames were coming out of the window and walls,' he said.

The size of the fire meant the unit had to call for backup.

