'The CFA proceeded to fight the fire from the exterior and hosing down the building. Then neighbouring crews arrived with breathing apparatus.' 

It took fire crews more than half an hour to put out the blaze. There was fairly extensive damage, with an estimated 70 to 80 percent of the house gutted. 

'The cause is being investigated but it's looking like possibly a heating appliance.' Mr Lawrence said. 

The cat's owner, Mr Jeeves, lost everything but escaped relatively unharmed.

He was treated for minor shock and smoke inhalation and will be staying with neighbours until he is able to rebuild the property. 

'I'm happy to be alive but you can't replace the memories,' he said.

